
[1]ghostly

   GHOSTLY, a. Spiritual; relating to the soul; not carnal or secular.

   Save and defend us from our ghostly enemies.

   1. Spiritual; having a character from religion; as a ghostly father.

   2. Pertaining to apparitions.
